tell us about the conduct
of international relations?

00:53:21.910 --> 00:53:25.170
How can our understanding
of visual cognition

00:53:26.090 --> 00:53:29.710
lead to insight about
sculpture and painting?

00:53:29.710 --> 00:53:33.490
How does auditory analysis mesh

00:53:33.490 --> 00:53:35.200
with our understanding of music?

00:53:35.200 --> 00:53:37.180
Can there be understandings of poetics

00:53:37.180 --> 00:53:40.930
and literary style that are
informed by linguistics?

00:53:40.930 --> 00:53:44.730
Now many scholars in the
humanities just have a hissy fit

00:53:44.730 --> 00:53:45.630
when they hear about this.

00:53:45.630 --> 00:53:47.800
They think it's a
reductionist, scientistic,

00:53:47.800 --> 00:53:50.340
determinist, positivist, atavist,

00:53:50.340 --> 00:53:53.760
and I think that attitude
is sealing the doom

00:53:53.760 --> 00:53:54.770
of the humanities.

00:53:54.770 --> 00:53:56.670
I think there're tremendous opportunities

00:53:56.670 --> 00:53:59.160
for mutual benefit on each side,

00:53:59.160 --> 00:54:02.060
and I hope that the
universities will be a place

00:54:02.060 --> 00:54:05.590
in which these opportunities
for insight are explored.

00:54:05.590 --> 00:54:07.620
- And one final question.

00:54:07.620 --> 00:54:12.620
If students watching this interview were

00:54:12.810 --> 00:54:17.403
to find insight from your
intellectual journey,

00:54:19.020 --> 00:54:21.210
what should they learn from your journey?

00:54:21.210 --> 00:54:25.780
And how would you advise them
to prepare for the future?

00:54:25.780 --> 00:54:27.020
- Certainty to...

00:54:28.470 --> 00:54:30.380
I'm giving some somewhat
contradictory advice.

00:54:30.380 --> 00:54:34.730
One of them, one piece
dealing with the realities

00:54:34.730 --> 00:54:36.680
of the academic scene as it exists,

00:54:36.680 --> 00:54:40.120
the other of holding out
hope for changing it.

00:54:40.120 --> 00:54:43.350
So the reality is disciplines are here.

00:54:43.350 --> 00:54:45.870
You wanna get employed,
you wanna get tenure,

00:54:45.870 --> 00:54:48.099
respect the disciplines.

00:54:48.099 --> 00:54:48.932
On the other hand,

00:54:48.932 --> 00:54:50.470
I think that's a deplorable
state of affairs,

00:54:50.470 --> 00:54:51.630
though it is the reality,

00:54:51.630 --> 00:54:53.640
and is if you wanna play your part

00:54:53.640 --> 00:54:58.350
in trying to overcome
this unfortunate legacy,

00:54:58.350 --> 00:55:00.010
immerse yourself in other disciplines,

00:55:00.010 --> 00:55:03.950
Be interested in topics, ideas, problems,

00:55:03.950 --> 00:55:07.493
phenomena not in academic guilds.

00:55:08.660 --> 00:55:10.450
Negotiating those two, I mean,

00:55:10.450 --> 00:55:12.100
that's one of the great
things about tenure.

00:55:12.100 --> 00:55:14.450
Once you have tenure, it
does give you the freedom

00:55:14.450 --> 00:55:18.473
to peer into what's going on
in the next guy's discipline.

